---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
---

<Layout title="Materials & Finishes">
  <Header />
  
  <section class="page-header" style="background-color: var(--color-charcoal); color: var(--color-off-white); text-align: center; padding: var(--spacing-xxl) 0;">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 style="color: var(--color-off-white);">Materials & Finishes</h1>
      <p style="font-size: 1.25rem; max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto;">Understanding the substrate and surface treatments that define our work.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <main class="container section">
    <div class="intro-text" style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto var(--spacing-xl); text-align: center;">
      <p>The foundation of every custom piece is the material itself. We specialize in working with architectural-grade metals, each offering unique structural properties and aesthetic possibilities. Our finishing techniques range from time-honored chemical patinas to state-of-the-art powder coatings.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Base Metals -->
    <h2 class="section-title">Base Metals</h2>
    <div class="grid material-grid">
      <div class="material-card">
        <img class="color-swatch-img" src="/images/steel.jpg" alt="Mild & Hot-Rolled Steel" />
        <h3>Mild & Hot-Rolled Steel</h3>
        <p>The workhorse of architectural fabrication. Offers immense strength and a beautiful, organic "mill scale" texture when left exposed. Ideal for structural railings, monumental stairs, and raw industrial aesthetics.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="material-card">
        <img class="color-swatch-img" src="/images/brass.jpg" alt="Architectural Brass & Bronze" />
        <h3>Architectural Brass & Bronze</h3>
        <p>Living materials that age gracefully over time. Brass brings a warm, luxurious glow to any space, while bronze offers deep, sculptural permanence. Perfect for high-end hardware, handrails, and accents.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="material-card">
        <img class="color-swatch-img" src="/images/aluminum.jpg" alt="Aluminum" />
        <h3>Aluminum</h3>
        <p>Lightweight and inherently corrosion-resistant. Aluminum is our preferred substrate for exterior gates, outdoor furniture, and coastal environments where saltwater degradation is a concern.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <hr class="divider" style="margin: var(--spacing-xxl) auto;" />

    <!-- Finishes & Patinas -->
    <h2 class="section-title">Finishes & Patinas</h2>
    <div class="grid finish-grid">
      <div class="finish-item">
        <div class="finish-image" style="background-color: #1A1A1A;"></div>
        <h4>Matte Black Powder Coat</h4>
        <p>A baked-on, highly durable finish that resists scratching, chipping, and fading. Offers a clean, modern aesthetic with zero maintenance. Suitable for both indoor and outdoor use.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="finish-item">
        <div class="finish-image" style="background: linear-gradient(45deg, #2a1610, #4d2b18);"></div>
        <h4>Statuary Bronze Patina</h4>
        <p>A chemical oxidation process applied to brass or bronze that artificially ages the metal, resulting in deep, rich brown tones with subtle variations. Waxed for interior protection.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="finish-item">
        <div class="finish-image" style="background: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #B88B4A, #B88B4A 10px, #d4af37 10px, #d4af37 20px);"></div>
        <h4>Satin Brushed Brass</h4>
        <p>A physical finish where the metal is linearly abraded to create a soft, non-reflective sheen. Often sealed with a clear lacquer to prevent natural tarnishing, maintaining its bright luxury.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="finish-item">
        <div class="finish-image" style="background: radial-gradient(circle, #555 0%, #222 100%);"></div>
        <h4>Blackened Steel</h4>
        <p>A chemical treatment applied directly to raw steel that turns the surface a deep gunmetal-to-black color while allowing the natural grain and mill scale to show through. Sealed with penetrol or wax.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div style="text-align: center; margin-top: var(--spacing-xl);">
      <p style="font-family: var(--font-heading); font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);">Need physical samples for a client presentation?</p>
      <a href="/contact" class="btn">Request a Sample Box</a>
    </div>

  </main>

  <footer class="bg-dark" style="padding: var(--spacing-lg) 0; text-align: center;">
     <p style="color: var(--color-off-white); margin: 0;">&copy; {new Date().getFullYear()} The Urban Forge. All rights reserved.</p>
  </footer>
</Layout>

<style>
  .section-title {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);
    position: relative;
    padding-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .section-title::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 0;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translateX(-50%);
    width: 80px;
    height: 3px;
    background-color: var(--color-brushed-brass);
  }
  
  .material-grid {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
  }
  
  .material-card {
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid #eaeaea;
    padding: var(--spacing-lg);
    border-radius: 4px;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
    transition: transform 0.3s ease;
  }
  .material-card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-5px);
    border-color: var(--color-brushed-brass);
  }
  
  .color-swatch-img {
    height: 150px;
    width: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    border-radius: 4px;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
    border: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
    display: block;
  }
  
  .finish-grid {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
  }
  
  .finish-item {
    text-align: center;
  }
  
  .finish-image {
    width: 150px;
    height: 150px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    margin: 0 auto var(--spacing-md);
    border: 3px solid #fff;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
  }
  
  h3, h4 {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  
  .divider {
    border: 0;
    height: 1px;
    background: #e0e0e0;
    max-width: 200px;
  }
</style>
